<subSubSection id="9ECC98D7C750FF9A43ADBEEA6417FC69" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D669CB5CC750FF9A43ADBEEA6417FC69" blockId="1.[151,1437,730,1009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC750FF9A43ADBEEA6474FD6C" bold="true" box="[151,274,730,756]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Members of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC750FF9A417EBEEB67D0FD6C" box="[580,694,731,756]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acrotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Dimetrota">
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC750FF9A417EBEEB67D0FD6C" box="[580,694,731,756]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Dimetrota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other subgenera of 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC750FF9A47FEBEEB606BFD6D" box="[1220,1293,731,757]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC750FF9A47FEBEEB606BFD6D" box="[1220,1293,731,757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="402">Atheta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characters: lateral regions of body and tibiae with conspicuously long and strong setae; infraorbital carina complete; ligula divided into two lobes in basal half; pronotum with rather narrow and asperate punctation, with conspicuous and long setae in lateral margins, pubescence directed anteriorly in midline; mesocoxal cavities narrowly separated; elytra with asperate punctation; at suture subequal to length of pronotum at middle; abdomen with sparse punctation to apex; abdominal tergite II with 2 macrosetae on each side of midline, III with anterior macrosetae; macrochaetal arrangement of VII 34 (
<bibRefCitation id="B247B6ADC750FF9A40B2BF8361EBFC55" author="Benick, G. &amp; Lohse, G. A." box="[904,1165,947,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" pagination="72 - 220" refId="ref8579" refString="Benick, G. &amp; Lohse, G. A. (1974) [Tribus 14 (Callicerini)]. In: Freude, H., Harde, K. W. &amp; Lohse, G. A. (Eds.), Die Kafer Mitteleuropas. Band 5. Staphylinidae II (Hypocyptinae und Aleocharinae), Pselaphidae. Goecke and Evers Verlag, Krefeld, pp. 72 - 220." type="book chapter" year="1974">Benick &amp; Lohse, 1974</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B247B6ADC750FF9A47A2BF8360F1FC55" author="Yosii, R. &amp; Sawada, K." box="[1176,1431,947,973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" pagination="11 - 140" refId="ref9886" refString="Yosii, R. &amp; Sawada, K. (1976) Studies on the genus Atheta Thomson and its allies (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). II: Diagnostic characters of genera and subgenera with description of representative species. Contributions from the Biological Laboratory, Kyoto University, 25 (1), 11 - 140." type="journal article" year="1976">Yosii &amp; Sawada, 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B247B6ADC750FF9A43ADBFE76403FC69" author="Lohse, G. A. &amp; Klimaszewski, J. &amp; Smetana, A." box="[151,357,983,1009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="402" pagination="121 - 202" refId="ref9316" refString="Lohse, G. A., Klimaszewski, J. &amp; Smetana, A. (1990) Revision of arctic Aleocharinae of North America (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 44, 121 - 202." type="journal article" year="1990">
